"""2D Rendering Engine — Multi-Backend 2D Graphics

@tag:stdlib
@tag:api
@tag:gpu

A multi-backend 2D rendering engine providing an abstract rendering interface.
Each backend implements the same RenderBackend trait. The engine auto-selects
the best available backend at runtime.

## Architecture

    Apps -> UI Lib -> Browser Engine -> 2D Engine -> Backend

Backends (in priority order):
  1. CUDA   — GPU-accelerated via CUDA kernels (NVIDIA)
  2. Vulkan — Cross-platform GPU (stub, future)
  3. OpenGL — Legacy GPU (stub, future)
  4. Software — Optimized CPU with tile-based rendering + alpha blending
  5. CPU    — Pure software fallback (always available)

## Quick Start

    use std.gpu.engine2d.{Engine2D}
    use std.gpu.engine2d.color.{rgb, color_white}

    var engine = Engine2D.create(800, 600)
    engine.clear(color_white())
    engine.draw_rect_filled(10, 10, 200, 100, rgb(255, 0, 0))
    engine.draw_text(20, 40, "Hello!", rgb(0, 0, 0), 14)
    engine.present()

## Layer Compositing

    use std.gpu.engine2d.compositor.{Compositor, Layer}

    var compositor = Compositor.create()
    var bg = Layer.create(0, 0, 800, 600)
    bg.fill(rgb(200, 200, 200))
    compositor.add_layer(bg)

    var fg = Layer.create(100, 100, 200, 200)
    fg.opacity = 0.7
    compositor.add_layer(fg)
    compositor.composite_to_buffer(engine.read_pixels(), 800, 600)

## Submodules

  - backend:          RenderBackend trait (abstract interface)
  - backend_cpu:      Pure software CPU renderer (always available)
  - backend_cuda:     CUDA GPU renderer (NVIDIA GPUs)
  - backend_vulkan:   Vulkan GPU renderer (stub)
  - backend_opengl:   OpenGL GPU renderer (stub)
  - backend_software: Optimized software renderer (tile-based, alpha blend)
  - engine:           Engine2D facade with auto-detection
  - color:            Color packing, blending, interpolation, hex conversion
  - compositor:       Layer-based compositing with alpha blend
"""

# Re-export public API from submodules
use std.gpu.engine2d.engine.{Engine2D}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend.{RenderBackend}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend_cpu.{CpuBackend}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend_cuda.{CudaBackend}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend_vulkan.{VulkanBackend}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend_opengl.{OpenGLBackend}
use std.gpu.engine2d.backend_software.{SoftwareBackend}
use std.gpu.engine2d.color.{
    rgba, rgb, color_r, color_g, color_b, color_a,
    blend, lerp_color, hex_to_color, color_to_hex,
    color_black, color_white, color_red, color_green, color_blue,
    color_yellow, color_cyan, color_magenta, color_transparent, color_gray
}
use std.gpu.engine2d.compositor.{Layer, Compositor}
